Prerequisites

Make sure you have python3 installed on your system. 

To install:

1) mkdir ~/.myPrograms (if it doesn't already exist)
2) cd ~/.myPrograms
3) Make sure that TableToLatex.sh is an executable
4) ln -s route/directory/for/TableToLatex.sh TableToLatex
5) Add the following line at the end of your .bashrc (or .zshrc ...):

             export PATH=$PATH:~/.myPrograms

Any new terminal (or after sourcing the current one) should be able to
run TableToLatex.

To run TableToLatex you should introduce the table through a pipe, e.g.:

cat Outfile.txt | TableToLatex

and you should obtain LatexTableFile.tex.

WARNING: This script overwrites to the same file. Please, 
rename the file after being created.

